{"type":"message","id":"b9a9e399","parentId":"6eb0fe60","timestamp":"2026-04-07T05:33:58.746Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The user wants to know what the war update contains. I need to provide the actual war update content that was generated by the cron job. Let me check if there's a way to retrieve it. The cron job runs a script that creates an agentTurn to generate the war update and send it via message. Since it was delivered successfully, I should be able to see it in the session history if it was sent as a message to this session, or I might need to check if it was sent as a direct message (which would appear in this session's history since this is the direct session with Nemesis).\n\nLooking at the session history, I see many of my own thoughts and tool calls, but I need to look for actual message content that was sent as a result of the war update cron job. Let me examine the session history more carefully for any messages that might contain the war update.\n\nActually, I should check if there's a way to get the output of the cron job directly. The cron job runs a script that creates another cron job (the temporary execution job) which runs the agentTurn. That agentTurn should have generated the war update and sent it via message. Since the delivery was set to \"announce\" with channel telegram and to 7924461837, it should have sent a message to this session.\n\nLet me look through the session history for any messages that might contain the war update. I'll look for recent assistant messages that aren't just my thinking processes.\n\nActually, let me check the session history again but focus on the actual content messages, not the thinking or tool calls. Let me get the session history and extract just the message content.\n","thinkingSignature":"reasoning"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"chatcmpl-tool-a4a6184940b80ddc","name":"sessions_history","arguments":{"sessionKey":"agent:main:telegram:direct:7924461837","limit":100