d I don't see any message output in the session history, there are a few possibilities: 1. The temporary job ran but failed to send the message 2. The temporary job ran and sent the message, but the message didn't appear in the session history for some reason 3. The temporary job hasn't run yet (maybe there was a delay) 4. The temporary job ran but encountered an error Let me check if there are any errors in the cron jobs or if I can see any output from the script execution. Actually, let me check the output of the daily-war-update job itself. When I ran it, I got \\\"ok\\\": true, \\\"enqueued\\\": true. That means the cron job was successfully created. But I didn't see the output of the script itself. Let me check if there's a way to see the s\\n…(truncated)…\"\n        },\n        {\n          \"type\": \"toolCall\",\n          \"id\": \"chatcmpl-tool-a6c9d41e934de3d7\",\n          \"name\": \"exec\",\n          \"arguments\": {\n            \"command\": \"cd /root/.openclaw/workspace && python3 scripts/daily_war_update.py\"\n          }\n        }\n      ],\n      \"api\": \"openai-completions\",\n      \"provider\": \"kilocode\",\n      \"model\": \"nvidia/nemotron-3-super-120b-a12b:free\",\n      \"stopReason\": \"toolUse\",\n      \"timestamp\": 1775540208933,\n      \"responseId\": \"gen-1775540209-JjkKMi8FvT4KNKZxHIp4\",\n      \"__openclaw\": {\n        \"id\": \"b635f03b\",\n        \"seq\": 60\n      }\n    },\n    {\n      \"role\": \"assistant\",\n      \"content\": [\n        {\n          \"type\": \"thinking\",\n          \"thinking\": \"We have to wait for the temporary job to run and then check if it produced any output. Let me wait a bit and then check the cron jobs list again to see if the temporary job appeared and ran. Actually, let me check if there are any new cron jobs that were created recently. Let me list cron jobs again and look for any job with \\\"execution\\\" in the name or similar. Let me also check if there are any recent cron job runs that I missed. Let me do that now.\\n\"\n        },\n        {\n          \"type\": \"toolCall\",\n          \"id\": \"chatcmpl-tool-894b02f416b2b945\",\n          \"name\": \"cron\",\n          \"arguments\": {\n            \"action\": \"list\"\n          }\n        }\n      ],\n      \"api\": \"openai-completions\",\n      \"provider\": \"kilocode\",\n      \"model\": \"nvidia/nemotron-3-super-120b-a12b:free\",\n      \"stopReason\": \"toolUse\",\n      \"timestamp\": 1775540315931,\n      \"responseId\": \"gen-1775540316-z7mmyUlbaNgOgDuHnniz\",\n      \"__openclaw\": {\n        \"id\": \"710dd5fe\",\n        \"seq\": 62\n      }\n    },\n    {\n      \"role\": \"assistant\",\n      \"content\": [\n        {\n          \"type\": \"thinking\",\n          \"thinking\": \"Let me wait a bit more for the execution job to run. Let me check if it has run by looking at its state or checking for any new cron jobs that might have been created by it. Actually, let me check if there are any new messages in the session that might contain the war update. Let me wait a moment and then check the session history again for any new assistant messages that might contain the war update.\\n\\nActually, let me check if the execution job has run by looking at its state. I see it has a nextRunAtMs of 1775540345724 which is in the future (about 30 seconds from creation time). Let me wait a bit and then check if it has run.\\n\\nLet me wait 40 seconds and then check the cron jobs again to see if the execution job has run and been deleted (since it has deleteAfterRun: true).\\n\\nActually, let me check the current time to see how long to wait. The creation time was 1775540315804 milliseconds since epoch. Let me convert that to a readable time to see how long ago it was created.\\n\\nBut for now, let me just wait a moment and then check the cron list again to see if the execution job is still there or if it has been deleted after running.\\n\\nLet me wait 30 seconds and then check.\\n\"\n        },\n        {\n          \"type\": \"toolCall\",\n          \"id\": \"chatcmpl-tool-ac5523585fbaf206\",\n          \"name\": \"cron\",\n          \"arguments\": {\n            \"action\": \"list\"\n          }\n        }\n      ],\n      \"api\": \"openai-completions\",\n      \"provider\": \"kilocode\",\n      \"model\": \"nvidia/nemotron-3-super-120b-a12b:free\",\n      \"stopReason\": \"toolUse\",\n      \"timestamp\": 1775540334280,\n      \"responseId\": \"gen-1775540335-Nyw9yVcyZlucTNOqtG27\",\n      \"__openclaw\": {\n        \"id\": \"5471cf6d\",\n        \"seq\": 64\n      }\n    },\n    {\n      \"role\": \"assistant\",\n      \"content\": [\n        {\n          \"type\": \"thinking\",\n          \"thinking\": \"The user is asking for the war update content. The daily-war-update-execution job is currently running (runningAtMs is set). I should wait for it to complete and then check if it has sent the result. Since it was set to run at 05:39:05 UTC (which is about 30 seconds from creation time), and it's now running, I should wait a bit more for it to complete. However, I can also check if there are any messages in the session that might contain the result once it's done. Let me wait a moment and then check the session history for any new messages that might contain the war update. Alternatively, I could check if the job has completed by looking at the cron list again in a moment. Let me wait a bit and then check. Since I can't actually wait in real-time, I'll check the cron list again to see if the job is still running or if it has completed. Let me do that now.\\n\"\n        },\n        {\n          \"type\": \"toolCall\",\n          \"id\": \"chatcmpl-tool-b24748d07b25f4a7\",\n          \"name\": \"cron\",\n          \"arguments\": {\n            \"action\": \"list\"\n          }\n        }\n      ],\n      \"api\": \"openai-completions\",\n      \"provider\": \"kilocode\",\n      \"model\": \"nvidia/nemotron-3-super-120b-a12b:free\",\n      \"