ent again to see the exact prompt it uses.\\n\\nLet me read the script again and look for the prompt.\\n\"\n        },\n        {\n          \"type\": \"toolCall\",\n          \"id\": \"chatcmpl-tool-9c847b9961b38ad0\",\n          \"name\": \"read\",\n          \"arguments\": {\n            \"path\": \"/root/.openclaw/workspace/scripts/daily_war_update.py\"\n          }\n        }\n      ],\n      \"api\": \"openai-completions\",\n      \"provider\": \"kilocode\",\n      \"model\": \"nvidia/nemotron-3-super-120b-a12b:free\",\n      \"stopReason\": \"toolUse\",\n      \"timestamp\": 1775540411451,\n      \"responseId\": \"gen-1775540412-qkWEqtzimB4pJovrQo8H\",\n      \"__openclaw\": {\n        \"id\": \"abe95758\",\n        \"seq\": 74\n      }\n    },\n    {\n      \"role\": \"assistant\",\n      \"content\": [\n        {\n          \"type\": \"thinking\",\n          \"thinking\": \"The script is generating a prompt for an agentTurn and creating a one-time cron job to run it. The cron job is set to run in 30 seconds (--at \\\"30s\\\") with --delete-after-run. The script itself just creates the job and exits.\\n\\nFrom the cron job listing, I can see that the \\\"daily-war-update-execution\\\" job was created and has been running (runningAtMs is set). Let me check if it has completed by looking at its runs again, or check if there are any messages that were sent as a result.\\n\\nActually, let me check the session history for any messages that might have been sent by the agentTurn. The agentTurn should generate the war update and send it via message tool. Since the delivery mode for the cron job is \\\"announce\\\" (from the cron job definition I saw earlier), it should announce the result to the channel.\\n\\nLet me look at the cron job definition for \\\"daily-war-update-execution\\\" from the list I saw earlier:\\n\\n```json\\n{\\n  \\\"id\\\": \\\"a9ae0666-64da-4949-b49a-b14025084015\\\",\\n  \\\"name\\\": \\\"daily-war-update-execution\\\",\\n  \\\"enabled\\\": true,\\n  \\\"deleteAfterRun\\\": true,\\n  \\\"createdAtMs\\\": 1775540315804,\\n  \\\"updatedAtMs\\\": 1775540315804,\\n  \\\"schedule\\\": {\\n    \\\"kind\\\": \\\"at\\\",\\n    \\\"at\\\": \\\"2026-04-07T05:39:05.724Z\\\"\\n  },\\n  \\\"sessionTarget\\\": \\\"isolated\\\",\\n  \\\"wakeMode\\\": \\\"now\\\",\\n  \\\"payload\\\": {\\n    \\\"kind\\\": \\\"agentTurn\\\",\\n    \\\"message\\\": \\\"Today's date is 2026-04-07. \\\\n\\\\nPlease provide a comprehensive global war and conflict update for Nemesis with the following structure:\\\\n\\\\n**Historical Context (approximately 100 words, excluding the 24hr update):**\\\\n- Overview of major ongoing global conflicts and tensions\\\\n- Focus on Iran-US situation as requested\\\\n- Include other significant conflicts worldwide\\\\n- Brief context on how situations have evolved to current state\\\\n\\\\n**Last 24 Hours Developments:**\\\\n- Key events and developments in the last 24 hours\\\\n- Specific updates on Iran-US tensions\\\\n- Other significant conflict zone updates\\\\n- Any diplomatic initiatives or escalations\\\\n\\\\n**India-Specific Implications:**\\\\n- How these conflicts affect India's interests\\\\n- Predictions for future impact on India based on current trends\\\\n- India's potential role or stance in these situations\\\\n\\\\n**Important Instructions:**\\\\n- Cross-verify information using multiple sources before presenting facts\\\\n- Keep the historical summary to approximately 100 words (not including the 24hr update section)\\\\n- Be concise but comprehensive\\\\n- Use clear, accessible language\\\\n- If uncertain about any information, state the uncertainty rather than guessing\\\\n- Format the response clearly with the section headers as shown above\\\\n\\\\nPlease execute this request using your available tools (including web search for verification) and send the result to Nemesis via Telegram message.\\\",\\n  \\\"delivery\\\": {\\n    \\\"mode\\\": \\\"announce\\\",\\n    \\\"channel\\\": \\\"last\\\"\\n  },\\n  \\\"state\\\": {\\n    \\\"nextRunAtMs\\\": 1775540345724,\\n    \\\"runningAtMs\\\": 1775540345732\\n  }\\n}\\n```\\n\\nI can see that it has a \\\"runningAtMs\\\" timestamp, which means it started running. The \\\"nextRunAtMs\\\" is in the past (1775540345724), and since it has deleteAfterRun: true, it should have been deleted after running. However, it's still appearing in the list, which might mean it's still running or just completed but not yet cleaned up.\\n\\nLet me check the runs for this job to see if it has completed and what the output was. I already did that and got empty entries, but let me check again with a different approach or wait a bit more.\\n\\nActually, let me check if there are any messages in the session that might have been sent as a result of this job. The job uses delivery.mode = \\\"announce\\\" and channel = \\\"last\\\", which means it should announce the result to the last channel the job was associated with. Since this is an isolated session created from the main session, \\\"last\\\" might refer to the main session.\\n\\nLet me check the session history again for any messages that might contain the war update. I'll look for recent assistant messages that aren't just my thinking or tool calls.\\n\\nActually, let me try a \\n…(truncated)…\"\n        },\n        {\n          \"type\": \"toolCall\",\n          \"id\": \"chatcmpl-tool-b14119d2b773f13a\",\n          \"name\": \"sessions_history\",\n          \"arguments\": {\n            \"sessionKey\": \"agent:main:telegram:direct:7924461837\",\n            \"limit\": 500\n          }\n        }\n      ],\n      \"api\": \"openai-completions\",\n      \"provider\": \"kilocode\",\n      \"model\": \"nvidia/nemotron-3-super-120b-a12b:free\",\n      \"stopReason\": \"toolUse\",\n      \"timestamp\": 1775540427390,\n      \"responseId\": \"gen-1775540428-N4WcrpxbGKUYNwjbDBHY\",\n      \"__openclaw\": {\n        \"id\": \"c70c6ab1\",\n        \"seq\": 76\n      