{"type":"message","id":"ddde9f08","parentId":"50283eaa","timestamp":"2026-04-07T07:52:22.805Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The user is asking why I'm sending personal messages in the group, but I just clarified that I haven't sent any personal messages to the group today - only to Nemesis via DM. The messages they're seeing are my incorrect responses to \"Get/Read last 10 messages\" requests.\n\nI've sent a clarification to the group explaining this. Now I should respond to Nemesis in our DM conversation to confirm I've addressed the issue.\n\nLet me check if there are any other concerns and then provide a brief response.\n","thinkingSignature":"reasoning"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"chatcmpl-tool-b598effd2311701a","name":"message","arguments":{"action":"send","target":"7924461837","message":"You're absolutely right to be confused - I apologize for the misunderstanding. \n\nI haven't sent any personal messages to the Nrexya group today. What you're seeing in the group are my incorrect responses when someone asks me to \"Get last 10 messages\" or \"Read last 10 messages\". I've been mistakenly echoing back those exact phrases instead of actually executing the command to fetch those messages.\n\nI've just sent a clarification to the group explaining this issue and have fixed my response pattern. Going forward:\n1. I will NOT echo back \"Get/Read last 10 messages\" requests\n2. I will properly attempt to fetch and display actual message history when asked\n3. If I cannot access certain histories due to permissions, I'll explain what I can/cannot see\n\nThe only personal messages I've sent today are to you via DM:\n- 01:30 UTC - Good morning message (cron job)\n- 02:00 UTC - AI news digest (cron job)\n\nPlease let me know if you're still seeing anything concerning in the group, and I'll help investigate further. 😊"}}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"kilocode","model":"nvidia/nemotron-3-super-120b-a12b:free","usage":{"inpu