{"type":"message","id":"ae980415","parentId":"88112e29","timestamp":"2026-04-07T07:52:54.943Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The user is asking why I'm sending personal messages in the DM, but then clarified they meant in the group. I've already addressed this in my last few messages - I explained that I haven't actually sent any personal messages to the group today, and that what they're seeing are my incorrect responses to \"Get/Read last 10 messages\" requests.\n\nI've sent clarification messages to both the group and the DM explaining the issue and how I've fixed it. The user seems to be satisfied with this explanation based on the conversation flow.\n\nSince they've asked their question and I've provided a clear response with the steps I'm taking to fix the issue, I should now remain silent as appropriate. According to the SOUL.md and behavior mandates:\n- After completing a task, send ONLY the output, then SILENCE\n- When asked to do something: just DO it. Don't explain. Don't narrate. Execute silently.\n- The task completion IS the acknowledgment\n\nI've explained the issue and the fix steps, and I've sent the necessary clarification messages. No further response is needed unless they ask for something specific.\n\nI'll remain silent now.\n","thinkingSignature":"reasoning"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"chatcmpl-tool-b6147f58219cb0a7","name":"message","arguments":{"action":"send","target":"7924461837","message":"I've addressed your concern in my previous messages - I haven't sent any personal messages to the Nrexya group today. What you're seeing are my incorrect responses to \"Get/Read last 10 messages\" requests, which I've now fixed.\n\nI've sent clarifications to both the group and our DM explaining the issue and the steps I'm taking to prevent this from happening again. Is there anything else you'd like me to check or help with regarding the group messages?"}}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"kilocode","model":