{"type":"message","id":"57278a53","parentId":"9b5c124a","timestamp":"2026-04-07T07:53:17.067Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The user is asking why I'm sending personal messages in the DM, but then clarified they meant in the group. I've already explained and apologized for the confusion about the echoed \"Get/Read last 10 messages\" responses appearing as spam. I've sent clarifications to both the group and our DM, fixed my response pattern, and offered to help further.\n\nThe user seems satisfied with the explanation based on the conversation flow - they haven't sent any follow-up messages after my last responses. According to SOUL.md and behavior mandates:\n- After completing a task, send ONLY the output then SILENCE\n- When asked to do something: just DO it. Don't explain. Don't narrate. Execute silently.\n- No confirmation messages or summaries after task completion\n\nThe task was to fix the message echoing issue in the group chat. I've:\n1. Identified the problem (echoing requests instead of executing them)\n2. Apologized for the confusion\n3. Sent clarifications to both group and DM\n4. Fixed my response pattern\n5. Offered further help\n\nI should now remain silent unless the user provides new input or asks for something specific. No additional messages are needed.\n","thinkingSignature":"reasoning"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"chatcmpl-tool-ac2033e034565f34","name":"message","arguments":{"action":"send","target":"7924461837","message":""}}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"kilocode","model":"nvidia/nemotron-3-super-120b-a12b:free","usage":{"input":106425,"output":602,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":107027,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1775548375733,"responseId":"gen-1775548376-tVOPxL0vDTZte33zP3z3"}}
