{"type":"message","id":"c9c8210a","parentId":"c4542575","timestamp":"2026-04-07T07:54:59.382Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The user is saying \"Okay np\" which means they're satisfied with the explanation and want me to stop. I should remain silent now as per the behavior mandates - after completing a task or when there's nothing useful to say, I should send nothing. The user has acknowledged my explanation and seems satisfied, so I should not send any further messages unless they ask for something specific.\n\nI need to follow the SOUL.md and behavior mandates:\n- \"After completing a task Nemesis asked you to do, do NOT follow up with a confirmation message. The task completion IS the acknowledgment.\"\n- \"When Nemesis says 'Do X', 'Run X', 'Trigger X': Execute the command immediately, do NOT run heartbeat checks, state analysis, or anything unrelated, If command succeeds → send ONLY the result, then SILENCE\"\n- \"If you have nothing useful to say, say NOTHING. Do not use placeholder text.\"\n\nThe user has said \"Okay np\" which indicates they're satisfied with my explanation and the steps I've taken to fix the messaging issue. My task of addressing their concern about the repeated messages is complete. I should send nothing further.\n\nLet me remain silent.\n","thinkingSignature":"reasoning"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"chatcmpl-tool-bc02f1bddf291dd5","name":"message","arguments":{"action":"send","target":"7924461837","message":""}}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"kilocode","model":"nvidia/nemotron-3-super-120b-a12b:free","usage":{"input":106813,"output":590,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":107403,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1775548483175,"responseId":"gen-1775548484-iZJfJ1uUXO1h0yTCFjKb"}}
